Description          Description If you’ve ever written a screenplay then you surely already know that getting someone to both read it and provide helpful, detailed feedback can be just as difficult–if not more so–than the writing process itself.
After all, at a certain point what’s needed most is a set of fresh eyes That’s where we come in.
We’ll cover these categories in as much detail as makes sense for each script:  An overall summary covering specific strengths & weaknesses Characters Dialogue Concept Plot Formatting/Structure  Those offering the feedback are true fans of the genre and professionals in the film industry as producers, writers, critics, and instructors.
If you’re interested in getting the feedback ball rolling, please review the TERMS AND CONDITIONS, and fill out the necessary information.
We will reach out to you shortly!
